<p>Iran announced it is no longer bound by restrictions on its nuclear programme as the 2015 agreement reached with world powers hit its scheduled expiration, known as &quot;termination day&quot; [aljazeera.com#1][dawn.com#1]. Tehran said all deal provisions and related mechanisms are now considered terminated, while also stressing a continued &quot;commitment to diplomacy&quot; [dawn.com#1][timesofisrael.com#1]. European signatories pushed last month for the reimposition of UN sanctions, a move that effectively left the accord defunct, and nuclear talks are currently at an impasse [dawn.com#1][straitstimes.com#1]. Western governments have long alleged Iran seeks nuclear weapons, a claim Iran rejects, saying its programme is for civilian uses such as energy production [dawn.com#1].</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/DGoU6CS_h_tJfjjjbBtGJDqVLW8nMvd6gTdMzXTfpGBn7-KWScEezXs_BkvGxGb94T2KTGm201GyRu_FDj6Eg4Z4J9I4gf0k8pUUWYGNEUP3' alt='The Iranian flag outside the IAEA headquarters in Vienna, where the 2015 nuclear deal was signed.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Termination day: The deal’s UN-endorsed &quot;termination day&quot; fell on October 18, 2025, as set out under Security Council Resolution 2231 [dawn.com#1].</li><li>Past cap: Under the 2015 accord, Iran’s uranium enrichment was capped at 3.67% with strict oversight from the IAEA [dawn.com#1].</li><li>IAEA finding: The IAEA has reported Iran enriching uranium to 60%, unusually high for a state without a nuclear weapons programme [dawn.com#1].</li><li>Deal participants: The 2015 agreement included Iran plus China, Britain, France, Germany, Russia, and the United States [scmp.com#1][dawn.com#1].</li></ul><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>Iranian Foreign Ministry: Says all provisions and related mechanisms of the 2015 deal are terminated after expiry, while affirming Iran’s commitment to diplomacy. (<a href='https://www.dawn.com/news/1949723/iran-says-no-longer-bound-by-restrictions-on-its-nuclear-programme'>Dawn</a>)</li><li>European signatories (UK, France, Germany): Moved last month to reimpose UN sanctions linked to the deal, which effectively rendered the accord moot. (<a href='https://www.straitstimes.com/world/middle-east/premature-end-to-iran-nuclear-deal-after-reimposed-un-sanctions'>The Straits Times</a>)</li><li>International Atomic Energy Agency: Reported that Iran has enriched uranium to 60%, an unusually high level for a non-nuclear-weapon state. (<a href='https://www.dawn.com/news/1949723/iran-says-no-longer-bound-by-restrictions-on-its-nuclear-programme'>Dawn</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2025/10/18/iran-says-restrictions-on-nuclear-programme-terminated-as-deal-expires'>Iran says restrictions on nuclear programme ‘terminated’ as deal expires</a> - aljazeera.com</li><li><a href='https://www.timesofisrael.com/as-2015-deal-fizzles-out-iran-says-no-longer-bound-by-restrictions-on-nuclear-program/'>As 2015 deal fizzles out, Iran says no longer bound by ‘restrictions’ on nuclear program</a> - timesofisrael.com</li><li><a href='https://www.straitstimes.com/world/middle-east/premature-end-to-iran-nuclear-deal-after-reimposed-un-sanctions'>Premature end to Iran nuclear deal after reimposed UN sanctions</a> - straitstimes.com</li><li><a href='https://www.dawn.com/news/1949723/iran-says-no-longer-bound-by-restrictions-on-its-nuclear-programme'>Iran says no longer bound by ‘restrictions’ on its nuclear programme</a> - dawn.com</li><li><a href='https://www.scmp.com/news/world/middle-east/article/3329514/iran-says-no-longer-bound-restrictions-its-nuclear-programme-10-year-deal-ends'>Iran says no longer bound by ‘restrictions’ on nuclear programme as deal ends</a> - scmp.com</li></ul>